HEADWORD: abducent
<hw>abducent</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>a small
motor nerve supplying the lateral rectus muscle of the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> abducent nerve, abducens, nervus abducens, sixth
cranial nerve</syn>⟦br⟧
