HEADWORD: abducent
<hw>abducent</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr>
<fld>(physiol)</fld> <def>drawing away from the midline of the body or
from an adjacent part; -- especially of muscles</def>
<ant>adducent</ant>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> abducting</syn>⟦br⟧
